==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prolapse
<hw>Pro*lapse"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>prolapsus</ets>, fr. <ets>prolapsus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>prolabi</ets> to fall forward; <ets>pro</ets> forward +
<ets>labi</ets> to glide, fall.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The
falling down of a part through the orifice with which it is naturally
connected, especially of the uterus or the rectum.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prolapse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prolapse
<hw>Pro*lapse"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To fall down or out; to
protrude.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prolapsion</ent>⟦br⟧
